<subSubSection id="C33516AC1C14FFC1FF239AA83DEEB92A" pageId="8" pageNumber="563" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B9045271C14FFC1FF239AA83DEEB92A" blockId="8.[151,1437,417,586]" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">
<emphasis id="B95B99351C14FFC1FF239AA83D66BADA" bold="true" box="[151,273,417,442]" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B95B99351C14FFC1FEAE9AA83D19BAD9" box="[282,366,417,441]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">Female</emphasis>
. Marginal area of terga with broad basolateral membranous border. Scapal basin with distinct cross-ridge zone medially. Dorsal surfaces of head, mesosoma and metasoma without definite punctuation. Integument dull, with pulverulent air on vertex, pronotum and scutum. Dorsal surfaces of mesosoma and apical teeth of mandibles without reddish highlights. Metanotum pointed posteriorly. Tarsal claws with two subsidiary teeth. 
<emphasis id="B95B99351C14FFC1FF6F99383D62B929" box="[219,277,561,585]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">Male</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
