<figureCitation id="131459A21C14FFC1FC689EF33846BD73" box="[988,1073,1530,1555]" captionStart="FIGURES 19, 20" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1432,1455]" captionTargetBox="[168,1418,638,1411]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[162,1424,638,1411]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19, 20. Elampus pulchricollis, holotype, ♀. 19. Habitus, lateral view. 20. Pronotum, dorsal view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264651/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">
Fig. 
<number id="3DE757001C14FFC1FBA59EF23846BD73" box="[1041,1073,1531,1555]" pageId="8" pageNumber="563" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
); metasoma metallic green with large membranous whitish borders basolaterally; sterna greenish; wing membrane light with brown veins; femora and tibiae greenish; tarsi brownish. 
<emphasis id="B95B99351C14FFC1FD879D4B3E07BD3A" box="[563,624,1602,1626]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">Head</emphasis>
: scapal basin with distinct transverse zones of cross-ridging (
<figureCitation id="131459A21C14FFC1FA8C9D4B39F8BD3B" box="[1336,1423,1602,1627]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 24" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1553,1576]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,595,1532]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[219,1368,591,1532]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 24. Elampus pulchricollis. 21. T 3 apical margin, posterior view, punctures omitted on right side. 22. Metanotum, dorsal view, punctures omitted. 23. Metasoma, lateral view. 24. Head, frontal view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264652/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">
Fig. 
<number id="3DE757001C14FFC1FADB9D4A39F8BD3B" box="[1391,1423,1603,1627]" pageId="8" pageNumber="563" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
); scape and pedicel greenish; flagellomeres dark brown; malar space extremely short (about 
<number id="3DE757001C14FFC1FB4C9D6E396CBD1F" box="[1272,1307,1639,1663]" pageId="8" pageNumber="563" value="0.3">0.3</number>
× 
<collectionCode id="ED3EDDE21C14FFC1FAFE9D6E39E7BD1F" LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14382" box="[1354,1424,1639,1663]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14382" name="University of Modena and Reggio Emilia, Department of Biology" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">MOD</collectionCode>
); subantennal space narrow, shorter than 
<number id="3DE757001C14FFC1FDC69D833EE2BDC3" box="[626,661,1674,1699]" pageId="8" pageNumber="563" value="0.5">0.5</number>
× 
<collectionCode id="ED3EDDE21C14FFC1FD749D823F72BDC3" LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14382" box="[704,773,1675,1699]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14382" name="University of Modena and Reggio Emilia, Department of Biology" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">MOD</collectionCode>
; genal fringe well developed; genal region, behind the composed eye, with distinct scratch marks (
<figureCitation id="131459A21C14FFC1FD329DA73EADBDA7" box="[646,730,1710,1735]" captionStart="FIGURES 19, 20" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1432,1455]" captionTargetBox="[168,1418,638,1411]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[162,1424,638,1411]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19, 20. Elampus pulchricollis, holotype, ♀. 19. Habitus, lateral view. 20. Pronotum, dorsal view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264651/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">
Fig. 
<number id="3DE757001C14FFC1FD0F9DA63EADBDA7" box="[699,730,1711,1735]" pageId="8" pageNumber="563" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
); upper genal space broad (longer than 
<number id="3DE757001C14FFC1FB2F9DA738C9BDA7" box="[1179,1214,1710,1735]" pageId="8" pageNumber="563" value="2.5">2.5</number>
× 
<collectionCode id="ED3EDDE21C14FFC1FB6A9DA63953BDA7" LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14382" box="[1246,1316,1711,1735]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14382" name="University of Modena and Reggio Emilia, Department of Biology" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">MOD</collectionCode>
); posterior genal margin delimited by carina; upper frons with regular and deep punctures; vertex without punctuation; genal space with scarce and widely separated punctures. 
<emphasis id="B95B99351C14FFC1FD629DFE3F7CBC6E" box="[726,779,1783,1806]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">Legs</emphasis>
: fore femur elbowed basally, forming strong ventral keellike projection; tarsal claws with two subsidiary teeth; legs without distinct punctures, except by tiny ones noticed externally. 
<emphasis id="B95B99351C14FFC1FEA09C363D20BC36" box="[276,343,1855,1878]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">Wings</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis id="B95B99351C14FFC1FEDD9C363DFEBC37" box="[361,393,1855,1879]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">
R 
<number id="3DE757001C14FFC1FEC99C363DFEBC37" box="[381,393,1855,1879]" pageId="8" pageNumber="563" value="1.0">1</number>
</emphasis>
absent; 
<emphasis id="B95B99351C14FFC1FE5D9C363E77BC36" box="[489,512,1855,1878]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">M</emphasis>
strongly arched, arising slightly before at 
<emphasis id="B95B99351C14FFC1FC529C36386ABC36" box="[998,1053,1855,1878]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">cu–a</emphasis>
; 
<emphasis id="B95B99351C14FFC1FB999C36383EBC36" box="[1069,1097,1855,1878]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">Rs</emphasis>
short and curving away from distal margin of wing. 
<emphasis id="B95B99351C14FFC1FE2D9C6A3E7FBC1A" box="[409,520,1891,1914]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">Pronotum</emphasis>
: lower lateral pronotal surface with large and deep fovea; dorsal surface without punctuation, scarce punctures noticed antero and laterally (
<figureCitation id="131459A21C14FFC1FC9A9C8F3FF4BCFF" box="[814,899,1926,1951]" captionStart="FIGURES 19, 20" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1432,1455]" captionTargetBox="[168,1418,638,1411]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[162,1424,638,1411]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19, 20. Elampus pulchricollis, holotype, ♀. 19. Habitus, lateral view. 20. Pronotum, dorsal view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264651/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">
Fig. 
<number id="3DE757001C14FFC1FCD79C8E3FF4BCFF" box="[867,899,1927,1951]" pageId="8" pageNumber="563" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
); integument dull, with pulverulent air (
<figureCitation id="131459A21C14FFC1FAF19C8F3CC0BCA3" captionStart="FIGURES 19, 20" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1432,1455]" captionTargetBox="[168,1418,638,1411]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[162,1424,638,1411]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19, 20. Elampus pulchricollis, holotype, ♀. 19. Habitus, lateral view. 20. Pronotum, dorsal view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264651/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">Fig. 19, 20</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B95B99351C14FFC1FF649CA33D14BCA2" box="[208,355,1962,1986]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">Mesopleuron</emphasis>
: omaulus and scrobal carina very sharp; mesopleural surface coarsely punctuated. 
<emphasis id="B95B99351C14FFC1FAF49CA239ECBCA2" box="[1344,1435,1963,1986]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">Scutum:</emphasis>
notauli absent (
<figureCitation id="131459A21C14FFC1FEFA9CC73DD0BC87" box="[334,423,1998,2023]" captionStart="FIGURES 19, 20" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1432,1455]" captionTargetBox="[168,1418,638,1411]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[162,1424,638,1411]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19, 20. Elampus pulchricollis, holotype, ♀. 19. Habitus, lateral view. 20. Pronotum, dorsal view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264651/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">
Fig. 
<number id="3DE757001C14FFC1FE339CC63DD0BC87" box="[391,423,1999,2023]" pageId="8" pageNumber="563" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
); dorsal surface without punctuation along scutal area, scarce punctation restricted to posterolateral region; disc with integument dull, with pulverulent air (
<figureCitation id="131459A21C15FFC0FC709B9E386BBBD0" box="[964,1052,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 19, 20" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1432,1455]" captionTargetBox="[168,1418,638,1411]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[162,1424,638,1411]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19, 20. Elampus pulchricollis, holotype, ♀. 19. Habitus, lateral view. 20. Pronotum, dorsal view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264651/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">
Fig. 
<number id="3DE757001C15FFC0FC489B91386BBBD0" box="[1020,1052,152,176]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B95B99351C15FFC0FB869B9038C6BBD0" box="[1074,1201,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">Metanotum</emphasis>
: pointed posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="131459A21C15FFC0FF2B9BB53C81BBB4" box="[159,246,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 24" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1553,1576]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,595,1532]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[219,1368,591,1532]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 24. Elampus pulchricollis. 21. T 3 apical margin, posterior view, punctures omitted on right side. 22. Metanotum, dorsal view, punctures omitted. 23. Metasoma, lateral view. 24. Head, frontal view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264652/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">
Fig. 
<number id="3DE757001C15FFC0FF629BB53C81BBB4" box="[214,246,188,212]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
); coarsely punctuated. 
<emphasis id="B95B99351C15FFC0FDB49BB53EFCBBB4" box="[512,651,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">Propodeum:</emphasis>
with sharp teeth basolaterally. 
<emphasis id="B95B99351C15FFC0FC429BB4381DBBB4" box="[1014,1130,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">Metasoma</emphasis>
: lateral margins of visible terga with large membranous whitish border (
<figureCitation id="131459A21C15FFC0FD149BD63E82BB98" box="[672,757,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 24" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1553,1576]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,595,1532]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[219,1368,591,1532]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 24. Elampus pulchricollis. 21. T 3 apical margin, posterior view, punctures omitted on right side. 22. Metanotum, dorsal view, punctures omitted. 23. Metasoma, lateral view. 24. Head, frontal view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264652/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">
Fig. 
<number id="3DE757001C15FFC0FD629BE93E82BB98" box="[726,757,224,248]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
); T 
<number id="3DE757001C15FFC0FCAB9BE93F5CBB98" box="[799,811,224,248]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564" value="3.0">3</number>
distal margin with shallow medial notch (
<figureCitation id="131459A21C15FFC0FAA49BD63914BB98" box="[1296,1379,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 24" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1553,1576]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,595,1532]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[219,1368,591,1532]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 24. Elampus pulchricollis. 21. T 3 apical margin, posterior view, punctures omitted on right side. 22. Metanotum, dorsal view, punctures omitted. 23. Metasoma, lateral view. 24. Head, frontal view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264652/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">
Fig. 
<number id="3DE757001C15FFC0FAF29BE93914BB98" box="[1350,1379,224,248]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
) and smooth integument; T 
<number id="3DE757001C15FFC0FE279A0D3DEABA7C" box="[403,413,260,284]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564" value="1.0">1</number>
and T 
<number id="3DE757001C15FFC0FE539A0D3D82BA7C" box="[487,501,260,284]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564" value="2.0">2</number>
with tiny and widely separated punctures, very shiny interspaces; fine punctuation at all metasoma (
<figureCitation id="131459A21C15FFC0FEE29A2E3DDFBA20" box="[342,424,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 24" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1553,1576]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,595,1532]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[219,1368,591,1532]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 24. Elampus pulchricollis. 21. T 3 apical margin, posterior view, punctures omitted on right side. 22. Metanotum, dorsal view, punctures omitted. 23. Metasoma, lateral view. 24. Head, frontal view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264652/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">
Fig. 
<number id="3DE757001C15FFC0FE3E9A213DDFBA20" box="[394,424,296,320]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
), larger and deeper on T 
<number id="3DE757001C15FFC0FD099A213EBDBA20" box="[701,714,296,320]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564" value="3.0">3</number>
, mainly anterolaterally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9045271C15FFC0FF739A453F31BA05" blockId="9.[151,1436,151,536]" box="[199,838,332,357]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">
<emphasis id="B95B99351C15FFC0FF739A453D4CBA05" bold="true" box="[199,315,332,357]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">Variation.</emphasis>
The species is known only from the 
<typeStatus id="5494FB851C15FFC0FD689A453F35BA05" box="[732,834,332,357]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33516AC1C15FFC0FF739A663E29BAE8" box="[199,606,367,392]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8B9045271C15FFC0FF739A663E29BAE8" blockId="9.[151,1436,151,536]" box="[199,606,367,392]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">
<emphasis id="B95B99351C15FFC0FF739A663DC7BAE8" bold="true" box="[199,432,367,392]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">Material examined.</emphasis>
<typeStatus id="5494FB851C15FFC0FE039A663E68BAE8" box="[439,543,367,392]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">Holotype</typeStatus>
only.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33516AC1C15FFC0FF739A9D3EBCBACC" box="[199,715,404,429]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B9045271C15FFC0FF739A9D3EBCBACC" blockId="9.[151,1436,151,536]" box="[199,715,404,429]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">
<emphasis id="B95B99351C15FFC0FF739A9D3D17BACD" bold="true" box="[199,352,404,429]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F33805B71C15FFC0FED39A9D3DDCBACD" box="[359,427,404,429]" name="Brazil" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(Minas Gerais) (
<figureCitation id="131459A21C15FFC0FDDF9A9D3EC9BACC" box="[619,702,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1559,1581]" captionText="FIGURE 12. Elampus spp. Distribution in South America." pageId="9" pageNumber="564">
Fig. 
<number id="3DE757001C15FFC0FD2B9A9D3EC9BACC" box="[671,702,404,428]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33516AC1C15FFC0FF739ABE3818B977" pageId="9" pageNumber="564" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9045271C15FFC0FF739ABE3818B977" blockId="9.[151,1436,151,536]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">
<emphasis id="B95B99351C15FFC0FF739ABE3D4CBAB0" bold="true" box="[199,315,439,464]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species is highly morphologically modified and easily distinguishable by the dull integument on vertex, pronotum and scutum. Additionally, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F3EA41C15FFC0FD059AD5387ABA95" authority="Ducke" authorityName="Ducke" box="[689,1037,476,501]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="564" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchricollis">
<emphasis id="B95B99351C15FFC0FD059AD53FDFBA94" box="[689,936,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">Elampus pulchricollis</emphasis>
(Ducke)
</taxonomicName>
is readily identifiable by the broad basolateral membranous whitish border on lateral margins of visible terga of metasoma.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
